A link to some sample JUnit/HTMLUnit code to test wsdl
<http://michael01612.spaces.live.com/blog/cns!2D894EF96C8FC0!2238.entry>
.   The wsdl represents the contract, so it is important to make sure it
is stable over time.   A simple JUnit/HTMLUnit test can ensure this, or
at least alert you to changes.  It makes a nice addition to functional
web service tests.  Especially useful if you have a lot of web services
in an SOA.
